(Translated by Google) The shop alone makes Lafayette worth a visit. Wonderful Cajun-Zydeco shed. Inside with a pretty big stage, on which there is something going on every evening. The musicians come in, add themselves to the list and then play for 20-30 minutes one after the other.  Very nice and hip service in all positions. There is of course also beer, plus small snacks to suck up.  If you want, you can also sit outside. But who wants that when the evenings are still almost 30 degrees in August.  (Original) Der Laden allein macht den Besuch in Lafayette lohnenswert. Wunderbarer Cajun-Zydeco Schuppen. Innen mit ziemlich großer Bühne, auf der jeden Abend was los ist. Die Musiker kommen rein, tragen sich in die Liste ein und spielen dann hintereinander weg so 20-30 Minuten.  Sehr nette und hippe Bedienung auf allen Positionen. Es gibt natürlich auch Bier, dazu kleine Snacks zum Aufsaugen.  Wer will, der kann auch draußen sitzen. Aber wer will das schon bei abends noch knapp 30 Grad im August.

I was given a laminated paper number to put on my table to show which table to deliver my food to. The card was SO GROSS. It looked like the card hadn't  been wiped off in weeks. The flavor of the dish was good but not worth the money or the wait. It was garnished with a little pile of rusty lettuce. Bartender was rude. I came to see a band so I paid $5 cover which was totally reasonable but the show started 30 minutes late--not a huge deal but worth noting. Overall I might come back for another show but I wouldn't order food and I'd try to interact with staff as little as possible.
